Heritage and references (not vendored into this repository):

  * FDTDX  (https://github.com/ymahlau/fdtdx) — MIT License.
    The JAX-based solver whose forward update equations, Yee-grid conventions,
    PML formulation, source/detector design, and material model inform this
    project. Used as the primary porting reference and CPU cross-check oracle.

  * MEEP   (https://github.com/NanoComp/meep) — GNU GPL v2+.
    Consulted for its subpixel-smoothing (anisotropic averaging) and
    near-to-far-field algorithms. Because MEEP is GPL, any code derived from
    MEEP's source must have its licensing reconciled by the owner before
    distribution. See docs/licensing.md.

Both references live as sibling directories (../fdtdx, ../meep) in the
development workspace and are intentionally NOT copied into this repository.
